-- Orascom May Bid for $3.2 Billion Serbia Telekom, Vecernje Novosti Reports
-- B y   M i s h a   S a v i c
-- 2010-12-02T08:19:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-02/egypt-s-orascom-mulls-serbia-telekom-bid-vecernje-novosti-says.html
Orascom Telecom Holding SAE  has
registered for sales documents through its parent company
Weather Investments SpA in the tender for a majority stake in
Serbia’s Telekom Srbija AD,  Vecernje Novosti  reported, citing
unidentified people in charge of the asset sale.  Weather Investments, expected to merge with Russia’s
VimpelCom Ltd., may also bid after  America Movil SAB ,  Deutsche
Telekom AG ,  Telekom Austria AG  and France Telecom SA also
expressed interest in the Serbian company valued at 2.43 billion
euros ($3.2 billion).  Telekom Srbija is 80 percent owned by the state and 20
percent by Greece’s  Hellenic Telecommunications Organizations
AS .  To contact the reporter on this story:
